# Fishmarket v3 – Project

## Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **React**: 19
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (`@import "tailwindcss"`, `@theme inline` in globals.css)
- **Icons**: Material Symbols via `material-symbols` npm package; use the `Icon` component from `@/components/Icon` with the `MaterialSymbol` type for icon names
- **Animations**: Framer Motion (`AnimatePresence` + `motion`) for entry/exit; CSS/Tailwind for micro-interactions. See `.cursor/rules/animations.mdc`.
- **Language**: TypeScript

## Conventions

- Use the App Router: `src/app/` for routes, layouts, and global styles
- Use path alias `@/` for imports under `src/`
- Prefer the shared `Icon` component for Material Symbols; icon names match [fonts.google.com/icons](https://fonts.google.com/icons) (e.g. `home`, `settings`, `favorite`)
- CSS variables: `--background` and `--foreground` for theming; dark mode via `prefers-color-scheme`
- Theme (Figma): `src/app/theme/` — `colors.css`, `aliases.css`, `borders.css`, `mapped.css` (surface/text/icons), `responsive.css` (typography + layout spacing), `animations.css` (duration/easing tokens + keyframes). Typography: `text-hero`, `leading-h1`, `var(--paragraph-spacing-h1)`. Layout: `p-layout-md`, `gap-layout-lg`, `var(--spacing-layout-*)`. Animations: `var(--duration-press)`, `var(--ease-spring)`, etc. See `.cursor/rules/animations.mdc`
- **Lib**: Shared utilities and SDK singletons live in `src/lib/`. Key modules:
  - `firebase.ts` — Firebase client SDK singleton (uses `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` env vars, safe for client and server)
  - `firebase-admin.ts` — Firebase Admin SDK singleton (server-only, uses `FIREBASE_ADMIN_*` env vars)
  - `firestore.ts` — Firestore helpers (`createListing`, `updateListing`)
  - `storage.ts` — Firebase Storage helpers (`uploadListingImages`, `uploadVariantImage`, `uploadAvatar`)
  - `routes.ts` — Centralized `ROUTES` constant (all app paths in one place). Always import from here instead of hardcoding path strings. See `.cursor/rules/routes.mdc`.
  - `schemas/` — Zod schemas (e.g. `listing.ts`, `post.ts`, `collection.ts`). See `.cursor/rules/forms.mdc` and `data.mdc`.
  - `constants/` — Domain constants (e.g. `post.ts` — `TRENDING_HASHTAGS`, `COVER_FRAME_COLORS`, `VISIBILITY_OPTIONS`, `INTERACTION_SETTINGS`).
- **Components**: Components live in `src/components/<ComponentName>/`. See `.cursor/rules/components.mdc` for documented components (API, usage, Figma source).
- **Responsive UI**: All UI must be responsive for both mobile and desktop. Use theme breakpoints and layout tokens (`responsive.css`, `var(--spacing-layout-*)`) so layouts, typography, and spacing adapt across viewport sizes. Test key flows at narrow (mobile) and wide (desktop) viewports.
- **Comments**: Comment only where it adds value — e.g. above a function, util, or non-obvious/complex logic. Avoid over-commenting; prefer clear names and structure over inline noise.

## Loading Strategy

- **Skeleton loading**: Data-dependent sections accept an optional `loading?: boolean` prop. When `true`, render skeleton placeholders matching the section's real layout (same dimensions, spacing, and element count). When `false` or omitted, render normally (return `null` when data is empty).
- **Skeleton component**: Use the shared `Skeleton` primitive (`@/components/Skeleton`) — a single `div` with `animate-pulse rounded bg-slate-100`. Consumers pass Tailwind dimension/shape classes (e.g. `h-20 w-20 rounded-full` for avatar circles, `h-[194px] w-full` for image blocks).
- **When to use**: Any section or page that depends on async data and would otherwise show nothing (return `null` or blank) during fetch. Skeleton shapes should match the real content's layout so the page doesn't shift when data arrives.
- **Page-level loading state**: Pages that fetch multiple data sources (e.g. homepage with `getSellers` + `getNewReleases`) should track a single `loading` boolean via `Promise.all(...).finally(() => setLoading(false))` and pass it to all data-dependent children.
- **Route-level loading**: Full-page spinners (e.g. `AuthGuard`, `shop/page.tsx` Suspense fallback) are still appropriate for route-level loading. Skeleton loading is for **section-level** content within an already-rendered page.

## Rules and skills

- **Keep rules and skills in sync (mandatory)**: Before finishing any change that does any of the following, you **must** update the relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (and skills if applicable) in the same change — do not leave rule updates for later or skip them.
  - Add, remove, or rename routes, route files, or route protection.
  - Add, change, or remove components, patterns, or conventions (e.g. new shared components, form patterns, data helpers, theme tokens).
  - Change stack, tooling, or dependencies (e.g. new lib, new rule file, Zod/form/animations conventions).
  - Change Firestore/API/data shapes, helpers, or documented behavior.
  If in doubt, treat the change as rule-affecting and update the matching rule file (e.g. `routes.mdc`, `components.mdc`, `data.mdc`, `forms.mdc`, `animations.mdc`, or this file).
